        "text": "Below, we've curated a list of virtually all the research about race and the U.S. criminal justice system that is available online.\n\nRacial discrimination in housing, sentencing, and policing frequently explains why data show stark disproportionalities in justice involvement for people of color, particularly Black people. The research below goes into more detail as to how — and why — people of color are overrepresented in jails, prisons, and non-carceral forms of punishment."
